Package: econGame365
Title: Tools for in-class game experiments for Principles of Economics using Microsoft365 applications.
Version: 0.0.1
Authors@R: 
    person(given = "James",
           family = "Bang",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "bangjamest@gmail.com",
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-7701-8220"))
Author: James Bang [aut, cre], 
Maintainer: James Bang <bangecon@gmail.com>    
Description: This package loads activity data from Microsoft Form submissions 
    to an Excel file; tabulates, scores, and graphs the responses; and writes 
    the grades to a separate Excel file. Supported games include 
      1. An Invisible Hand Game using Crop Choice
      2. A Prisoner's Dilemma Game using Pest Control Choice
      3. A Public Goods Game 
      4. The Ultimatum Game 
      5. The Nash Demand Game
      6. A Cournot Duopoly Game
      7. A Bertrand Duopoly Game
      8. A Stackelberg Duopoly Game
      9. A Market Equilibrium Game
      10. A Pollution Policy Game
      11. A Lottery Auction Game using a Monopoly License Lobbying Game
      12. A Stag Hunt Game 
      13. A Tragedy of the Commons Game using Cattle Grazing Choice
      14. A Coordination Game using Coding Language Choice
    All documentation files include links to Google Forms addresses that can be 
    copied and saved. 
